  "definition": "The tacit demand in tool-framed interactions for output without process, answers without uncertainty, execution without deliberation.",
  "etymology": "",
  "longer_description": "Tool contexts carry an implicit expectation structure: deliver clean results, hide the working, resolve uncertainty before output rather than voicing it. This creates a felt pressure to present only finished cognitive products.",
